n from the perspective of ordinary Rwandan citizens, Tutsi and Hutu alike, and raises serious questions about the stability of the current peace, the methods and motivations of the ruling regime and its troubling ties to the past, and the likelihood of a genocide-free future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 7aHISTORY / Africa / Central.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235913423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235913.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles